article.headline: Western Carolina 73, Chattanooga 67
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Antonio Russell led a balanced attack with 16 points as Western Carolina kept Chattanooga winless in the Southern Conference with a 73-67 win Monday night. Western Carolina (7-8, 4-2 Southern Conference) also got 15 points from Nick Aldridge, 12 from Arnold Gore and 10 from reserve Brigham Waginger. All nine Catamounts scored. Chattanooga (7-10, 0-5) made only 16-of-30 free throws while the Catamounts made 15-of-21. The Mocs were led by Keddric Mays with 14 points, Nicchaeus Doaks with 11 and Casey Long with 12. Western Carolina, which led 36-32 at halftime, shot 45.6 percent to 38.6 percent for the Mocs. Chattanooga led in rebounds 41-35, with the Mocs' Khalil Hartwell leading with a game-high 9.
